  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  wedge fracture or burst fracture with Thoraco-Lumbar Injury Classification and
             Severity (TLICS) score ≥ 4

          -  Single level fracture

          -  Less than 50% of spinal canal compromised

          -  Mild kyphosis or scoliosis

          -  Cobb's angle ≤ 25˚

          -  with or without neurological deficit

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  patients with multiple level fractures

          -  patients with more than 50% spinal canal compromise

          -  patients who needed anterior approach to decompress the canal

          -  patients who have fracture dislocation and / or marked kyphosis and scoliosis with
             Cobb's angle &gt;25⁰

          -  patients who needed 360⁰ fixation with long segment fixation to maintain the angle of
             correction.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
